userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: While Special Collections is the owner of the physical and digital items, permission to examine collection materials is not an authorization to publish. These materials are made available for use in research, teaching, and private study. Any transmission or reproduction beyond that allowed by fair use requires permission from the owners of rights, heir(s) or assigns. See: http://library.stanford.edu/spc/using-collections/permission-publish

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [identification of item], Stanford Songs and Songbooks collection (SC1319). Dept. of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.. Department of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Series 1: Bound and unbound songbooks, 1893-1956; Series 2: Individual songs, 1892-1930; and Series 3: Class yells, 1892-1950.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Bound and unbound songbooks titles include A DECENNIAL OF STANFORD SONG 1895-1905, STANFORD SONGS, A COLLECTION OF CARDINAL FAVORITES, STANFORD FOOTBALL SONGS, LAGUNITA SONGBOOK, and CALIFORNIA UNIVERSITY SONGS. Individual songs include both printed songs and manuscripts.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Previously classified in the Stanford University Publications and Ephemera Collection "4digit" collection.
